    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between pairing wine with wild salmon versus farmed salmon?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Wild salmon has a leaner texture and more intense, earthy flavor that pairs beautifully with crisp whites like Sancerre or light-bodied Pinot Noir from cooler climates. Farmed salmon's richer, fattier texture can handle fuller-bodied wines like oaked Chardonnay or even medium-bodied Rhône reds. The key is matching the wine's weight and intensity to the salmon's richness level.</p>
  </div>

