    <p class="text-gray-700">White wines should be served at 45-50°F, while light reds like Pinot Noir are best at cellar temperature (55-60°F). Avoid serving wines too cold with salmon, as this will mute the delicate flavors that complement the fish's natural oils. If your wine is too cold from the fridge, let whites warm up for 10-15 minutes and reds for 20-30 minutes before serving.</p>
  </div>

