    <p class="text-gray-700">Cedar plank cooking adds smoky, woody aromatics that call for wines with complementary earthy notes. Oregon Pinot Noir with its forest floor characteristics or a lightly oaked Chardonnay from Burgundy work exceptionally well. The wine's subtle oak aging echoes the cedar's influence while the acidity cuts through the salmon's richness.</p>
