  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">Is wine with salmon good for wine beginners?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Absolutely! Salmon's natural oils and mild flavor create a forgiving pairing that won't clash with most wines, making it ideal for beginners to experiment. Start with crowd-pleasing options like Pinot Grigio, unoaked Chardonnay, or light Pinot Noir. The salmon's richness provides a perfect canvas to understand how wine acidity and tannins interact with food.</p>
